The paper deals with coding theory, specifically with the construction of codes by lifting the ground field of perfect codes. This falls under the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the properties of completely regular codes, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The computation of intersection numbers is a topic in combinatorics (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the covering radius of codes, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CR) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
